About Oscar

Oscar’s aim in life, like all Grouches, is to be as sad and grouchy as possible and pass that feeling on to everyone else.

Oscar responds with a snarl when someone knocks on his trash can, inevitably interrupting him from a snooze or an essential activity.

He moans that he wants to be alone, but when he is completely alone, he is dissatisfied since there is no one around to irritate or complain to.

How to Buy?

Step 1
Create a wallet
Create a MetaMask or Trust Wallet using your desktop or mobile device. Your new wallet will allow you to buy, sell, send or receive our token.
Step 2
Send ETH to your Wallet
You can buy ETH on any exchange that trade cryptocurrency like Binance, Coinbase, etc. After purchase transfer your ETH to your wallet.
Step 3
Connect wallet to Uniswap
Go to Uniswap and click on 'connect wallet'. Select the token by using our contract address. Alternately you can click use the flooz interface as well.
Step 4
Swap ETH for our Token
You can now swap your ETH for our token $GROUCH on Uniswap. It will automatically reflect on your wallet.

The History

Carroll Spinney who once voiced Oscar and was a staple Sesame Street founder has retired after he was diagnosed with a neurological disorder called dystonia. He then passed away in 2019 leaving the legacy for Eric Jacobson who is the current Oscar voice we know today.
